broadcastPayload(address,bytes,bytes).details: allows state registry to send messages to multiple dst chains

params.message_: is the cross-chain message to be broadcasted
params.srcSender_: is the caller (used for gas refunds)

params.broadcastRegistryId_: is the id of the broadcast registry
params.superRegistry_: is super registry address for respective chain

estimateFees(bytes,bytes).details: returns the gas fees estimation in native tokens

params.message_: is the cross-chain message to be broadcasted

returns.fees: is the native_tokens to be sent along the transaction

receiveMessage(bytes).details: function to receive broadcasted messages via Wormhole SR's

setChainId(uint64,uint16).details: allows protocol admin to add new chain ids in future

params.ambChainId_: is the identifier of the chain given by the AMB NOTE: cannot be defined in an interface as types vary for each message bridge (amb)
params.superChainId_: is the identifier of the chain within superform protocol

setFinality(uint8).details: allows protocol admin to set broadcast finality

params.finality_: is the required finality on src chain

setReceiver(uint16,address).details: allows protocol admin to set receiver implementation on a new chain id

params.authorizedImpl_: is the implementation of the wormhole message bridge on the specified destination NOTE: cannot be defined in an interface as types vary for each message bridge (amb)
params.chainId_: is the identifier of the destination chain within wormhole

setRelayer(address).details: allows protocol admin to configure relayer (superform owned)

setWormholeCore(address).details: allows protocol admin to configure wormhole core contract

params.wormhole_: is wormhole address for respective chain

estimateFees(bytes,bytes).notice: estimation differs for different message bridges.
